      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if its a worn sensor or if i messed up the caliper or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A squealing noise after a brake job is a common, albeit annoying, problem. First, you should check the brake pads themselves, even though you just replaced them. Sometimes, a new pad isn't seated perfectly, or maybe a tiny bit of grit got lodged between the pad and the rotor. It's a simple check, but it's the most likely culprit, and you don't want to waste time digging through the whole system when a simple nudge will fix it. If you're not sure about the pads, you might want to give the caliper a good wiggle to make sure everything is seated tight.",
      "source": "target",
